Jeanette Chabalala, News24(File, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Bloemfontein &ndash; A Free State reverend has died after he was shot twice in the upper body by a group of armed men who demanded money during a fake roadblock, police said on Tuesday. &nbsp;According to Lieutenant Malebo Khosana, the incident happened at Odendaalsrus on Saturday evening.&nbsp; &nbsp;Motlalepule Leseba, 52, died on Monday evening after he was rushed to hospital in a critical condition.&nbsp; &nbsp;"It is alleged that Leseba and his son were stopped in Odendaalsrus road by what looked to them like a police roadblock," said Khosana.The men demanded money from the reverend and his son. The suspects shot the cleric twice and fled with two cellphones. His son was not injured. &nbsp;A case of murder was opened. No arrests had been made yet. &nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.